    "statement": "Under deployment-realistic (generic) elicitation only 1/3 reward scorers reliably detect G7 (95% CI above chance). The G7 blind spot is a property of NARROW critics — the symbolic linter and specialised document / aesthetic rewards all miss it — while a capable GENERAL-multimodal reward detects it; every scorer is meanwhile clearly sensitive to its in-taxonomy classes. This refines 'neural rewards are blind to G7' to 'narrow rewards are; a general VLM reward (like a prompted VLM, Result-1) is not' — and validates routing G7 to a VLM engine."
